IDIV




	
	REG
	memory
	




Signed divide.
Algorithm:
 
	 when operand is a byte:
	 AL = AX / operand
	 AH = remainder (modulus)
	 
 

 
	when operand is a word:
	AX = (DX AX) / operand
	DX = remainder (modulus)
	
 
 Example:MOV AX, -203 ; AX = 0FF35h
MOV BL, 4
IDIV BL      ; AL = -50 (0CEh), AH = -3 (0FDh)
RET



